sub_title: On a mission to make air-transport more sustainable. Your energetic partner to get stuff done. Connect, Create, Innovate.
summary:
Highly experienced people-manager with a track record in operational responsibility and program-management achieving bottom-line results. 

Working with people, realizing tangible and significant results whilst solving complex problems and delivering customer satisfaction *together* energizes me.

I Advise senior management on where to put the company’s tactical and operational focus in line with the company’s strategy.

I am Passionate about Innovation, Technology, Entre- and Intrapreneurship. 

Personal development is very important for me. I love craftsmanship and proving *them* wrong when they say it can't be done.

Edit: I love to build and maintain a network of inspiring people. So, please reach out to connect. *However*, please indicate in a message the rationale of your connection request. As I highly value relationship, please use introductions for our talks. Thanks!

Furthermore, it is the ideal place to be when you have research or product development in collaboration with one or more of the research departments at the faculty.

The Aerospace Innovation Hub has close links and collaborates with the other incubators in the region. Yes!Delft, ESA BIC, RHIA, UVV are just some examples.

The Aerospace Cluster of the Joint Interdisciplinary Project (JIP), will also make use of the Aerospace Innovation Hub. JIP is an exceptional opportunity for students to incorporate interdisciplinary teamwork into the Master. The students will work together with companies in technical innovation on a business case to create innovative impact. The projects are focused on integrated design or research assignments, in addition value adding, societal acceptance and engineering ethics. More information can be found on www.jointinterdisciplinaryproject.nl.

With a community manager dedicated to be the “linking pin” between the startups, students, researchers and industry we will work together to innovate aerospace! There will be in-house coaching for the Aerospace Engineering Startup Voucher winners. Furthermore lectures, workshops and events will be set up to inspire and stimulate interaction.

We are looking forward to this success and hope to be able to welcome you soon in our Aerospace Innovation Hub @TU Delft.

http://www.space-of-innovation.com/first-copernicus-accelerator-bootcamp', 'title': 'Mentor Copernicus Master Accelerator program', 'employment_type': None}]}, {'company': {'id': 2294209, 'name': 'CGI Nederland', 'logo': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C560BAQH31NCm95cY4A/company-logo_400_400/0/1611122350968?e=1700092800&v=beta&t=tg_F5PmrGc-uVg3n3JpPC49tjw3AwSEDS2cbVML34_U', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cgi-in-nederland/', 'employees': {'start': 1001, 'end': 5000}}, 'date': {'start': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}, 'end': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, 'profile_positions': [{'location': 'Rotterdam', 'date': {'start': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}, 'end': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, 'company': 'CGI Nederland', 'description': 'CGI Space: Veilige, betrouwbare en innovatieve oplossingen in de ruimtevaart

Softwaresystemen voor de ruimtevaart hebben ons al veel belangrijke toepassingen gebracht: exploratie van het heelal, aardobservatie, ondersteuning bij rampenbestrijding en betere navigatie. Met de groei van het aantal satellietapplicaties neemt ook hun betekenis toe. Ruimtevaartorganisaties zoeken continu naar mogelijkheden om hun investeringen meer ten dienste te laten komen van de samenleving. Ondertussen moeten ze zich echter ook wapenen tegen de diverse dreigingen waaraan satellietsystemen en –informatie steeds meer blootgesteld worden.

CGI heeft meer dan 36 jaar ervaring in het leveren van complexe, missiekritische systemen voor de ruimtevaart. Wij worden erkend als thought leader in de ontwikkeling en beveiliging van ruimtevaartapplicaties en werken nauw samen met diverse civiele ruimtevaartorganisaties, waaronder de European Space Agency (ESA). Daarnaast spelen we in Europa een leidende rol als het gaat om het grondsegment van militaire satellietcommunicatie.

Vanuit Nederland zijn we betrokken bij het Galileo-project, het Europese programma voor satellietnavigatie.
